summary: In this blog post, I share my three-tier framework for multitasking with agent harnesses: one focused foreground task, one or two lightly supervised background tasks, and as many automated shadow tasks as you want. I explain how each tier works, how notifications keep you in control, and why a simple priority list is still essential. I also discuss how to move tasks down the chain for more effortless productivity. Curious how this system could help you multitask better without feeling overwhelmed?
